algorithm_technique: Use a hash set to store seen elements; if an element is already in the set, a duplicate exists.
problem_summary_simple: Check if any number appears more than once in an array.
problem_summary_technical: Detect duplicates in an array by comparing array length to the size of a hash set containing its unique elements.
key_insights: Hash sets provide O(1) average time complexity for insertion and lookup.
Comparing the original array length to the set length is a concise way to check for duplicates.
This is a fundamental problem for understanding hash table applications.
